Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}.

Halve the @baguette{2} lengthways. Pop them into the #oven{}, cut-side up, to warm
through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the baguettes are warmed, spread the @cream cheese{48%g} over the cut side
of the baguette bases.

Top with @salad leaves{40%g} (as much or as little as you like).

Layer the @sliced Irish ham{80%g} and then the tomato slices on top of the
salad. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Close the sandwich with the top of the baguette.

Halve the baguette widthways and plate up.

> As much flavour as the beloved BLT, but with an exciting twist! Swapping
> lettuce for rocket and adding delicious cream cheese makes this
> easy-to-assemble lunch a real treat.